(00091395369,'2011-01-02','January',2011,0,'F',4,5,4,5,5,4,'Very comfortable and clean. Highly recommend.','Everything to say has already been said. Great staff, clean rooms, and very comfortable beds. So, Iâ€™d light to highlight great customer service from Lala. Every time I make a reservation to any hotel, I request non feather bedding because of my allergies. I simply cannot deal with donald or daffy. And every single time, the hotels over look this request. Lala read the request and personally checked the room as I unloaded the car to make sure that the geese were elsewhere. Thatâ€™s service people! Hotels with far more stars donâ€™t have that kind of accountability and person touch. I have no quarms about recommending this place. GPS totally missed this place so be sure to be on the side of katy freeway heading east toward the beltway. Its next to texas land and cattle and holiday inn. The sign is small and low to the ground.',1158926,00000000084),
(00091788074,'2011-01-05','December',2010,1,'F',4,4,4,4,3,3,'Clean, fabulous location, overpriced','Itâ€™s clean, the rooms are large, and the location--for a business traveler--canâ€™t be beat. But not worth the rack rate (over $180/nite) so stay only if you get a deal here.',286988,00000000099),
(00092726592,'2011-01-12','January',2011,2,'F',1,1,3,1,3,1,'STAY AWAY, NOT KIDDING','I am in the hotel as I speak, and spend my time on writing a review BECAUSE I have never been more disappointed with a hotel, let alone a Starwood property.  I travel 4 days a week for work, and think I have a pretty good grasp on the hotel scene in the US and can provide an objective comparison. This property, supposedly fresh off a renovation, looks like a sad, dingy, rundown place. Issues I have ran into during only 24 hours of being here: - Room key card machine broke down for about an hour. Unable to check in to room or go to the gym, had to have a guy escort me around with a master key - First room I got was next to the elevator banks. Huge bangs heard every 10min, had to ask them to switch my rooms, which I do say is a plus, they handled well and I got a room further from the elevators - This property of 21 or so floors has 4 very old and scary elevators. Donâ€™t be surprised that the average wait can easily be 10-15min to just get out of the building. Oh, and this morning 3 of the 4 elevators WERE OUT OF SERVICE, you can imagine the chaos it caused, and how fun it is to walk up and down to the 11th floor - No ironing board, no iron, no hairdrier, no luggage rack, no coat hanger of any sort in the room.... They must have done furnishing in a hurry... - Toilet overflow - The toilet appears to flush, and then 2min later everything that you thought you flushed down, appears again. Then if you are lucky, 3 or so flushes later, the stuff finally goes down... - Dirty (dark brown on the bottom) bathtub with lot of leftover hair hanging out in it, nasty; makes me question how clean is the rest of the room - Ordered one salad entree through room service, got a completly different salad entree. Ate it without complaint, but how hard is it to get one order right? I am glad I am checking out in 10 hours from this nightmare, before anything else breaks or goes wrong. Itâ€™s especially unfortunate because Starwood typically has excellent properties associated with its name, I highly suggest they revisit their choice. Travelers - save your money, if you are in the area go to the Aloft; nice, clean, and organized property.',99135,00000000091),
(00092874528,'2011-01-14','December',2010,0,'F',4,4,4,4,4,4,'Buen Hotel, cerca de las atracciones de Houst','Estuve hospedado en este hotel en diciembre 2010 por espacio de una semana. Las instalaciones estan bien, asi como las habitaciones, amplias y limpias. 2 camas matrimoniales, un sofa cama, un sillon reclinador, cocina equipada. El servicio de limpieza es una vez por semana, pero se pueden cambiar las toallas en la recepcion. Tiene muy cerca un Walmart, Target, Best Buy, para comer un Golden Corral. Se puede ir caminando a cada uno de estos sitios. El internet inalmabrico cuesta 4.99$ por toda la estadia y es rapido y funciono genial. La zona es segura, no vi nada extraÃ±o. Queda a 10 minutos del downtown de houston, de las atracciones como el parque hermann, los museos tambien queda cerca como 15 minutos en auto. El desayuno es muy basico y pobre, pan, mermelada queso crema y cafe, algo de frutas como manzanas y naranja. Tiene una impresora inalambrica en la recepcion donde poder imprimir cualquier documento. En general, la estadia fue bien.',107956,00000000006),
(00092876245,'2011-01-14','December',2010,0,'F',4,4,5,5,4,5,'Excelente hotel en San Antonio','Me quede en este hotel por dos noches en mi recorrido por texas. La habitacion es amplia y limpia, 2 camas matrimoniales, sofa cama, sillon reclinador y cocina equipada. Televisor de 42 pulgadas pantalla delgada y dvd. La ubicaciÃ³n es genial, es un area de puros hoteles muy bonita. esta cerca de El Alamo, Tower of the Americas y del River Walk, en auto es algo asi como 15 minutos. El desayuno es basico pero resuelve. Me volveria a alojar aca mismo. Para desayunar tiene cerca un IHOP donde la comida es muy buena. El internet inalambrico funciono bien.',108736,00000000006),
(00092876859,'2011-01-14','December',2010,0,'F',3,4,4,4,3,4,'Hotel en Dallas','Nos hospedamos el 24 de diciembre 2010 en este hotel en nuestro recorrido por Texas. La habitacion es comun a todos los extended stay deluxe, amplia y comoda, 2 camas grandes, sofa cama, mesa, cocina equipada, TV y DVD. El DVD no funcionaba, se reporto en recepcion pero por la fecha no tenian a nadie que revisara. Compre 3 peliculas en wlamart para ver con la familia y nos quedamos con las ganas. El hotel esta en una buena zona. No me gusto la ciudad, de todo el recorrido fue la menos llamativa, no volveria a Dallas.',109427,00000000006),
(00093423802,'2011-01-17','January',2011,0,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'I felt like I was staying with family that re','I went to all the hotels in the area to find the one that would accommodate my extended family and friends for my daughters wedding and this hotel was by far the best. It was everything they promised it would be and more. I would highly recommend having a weekend wedding in this hotel because the staff was very attentive and worked with our time crunch because it was a morning wedding. The hotel was set back off the freeway and it did not have a through street so I felt safe and secure.',1158926,00000000083),
(00093577301,'2011-01-18','December',2010,0,'F',4,4,4,4,4,4,'Buen hotel','Estuve hospedado 3 dias en este hotel. Tiene el comun denominador de esta cadena de hoteles: habitaciones amplias, comodas. Hubo 2 cosas desfavorables: Las camas son mas pequeÃ±as que las matrimoniales comunes (1.4 metros de ancho), en este viaje, estas fueron las camas mas incomodas. El otro punto es que el hotel tiene un olor a cigarrillo que se siente en todas partes, tuvimos que abrir un ambientador para ocultar el olor. La zona esta bien, esta a menos de 10 minutos del katy mills mall.',595438,00000000006),
(00093644828,'2011-01-18','January',2011,0,'F',4,5,4,4,5,4,'Pleasant surprise','This is a nice hotel with friendly staff. Not luxurious, but comfortable. The â€™â€™king sizeâ€™â€™ bed is a small king, so plan accordingly. It has nice little touches to make the rooms homey - little reflective paint under counter in bathroom so turning on the light at night is unnecessary; shelving in the tub to hold towels; hutch for microwave and refrigerator with room for storage. We ate the breakfast and it was good - not great, but as it was included in our price, we wonâ€™t complain. Sausage gravy and biscuits, eggs, bacon, cereals, fresh fruits, pastries, yogurt, french toast, pancakes, hash browns, coffee, juice, and am probably leaving something out. We received a special rate due to the meet we were attending and it included breakfast. Not sure we would have been as pleased otherwise, but for the $80 (including tax) we paid, it was beyond great.',1158926,00000000082),
(00094047849,'2011-01-22','January',2011,1,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'Best value for the highest quality and excell','The hote is immaculate! Rooms are very clean and the beds are so comfortable with down comforters and pillows. Every morning, we were greeted with a delicious breakfast bar filled with scrambled eggs, sausage, bacon, waffles, bagels, fruit, coffee, juice, cold cereal, hot cereal, and more--it was wonderful! Plus, we had free bottled water available to us at all times and they have a happy hour at 5pm where we would start our evening with a few glasses of wine and snacks. The staff was personable and helpful. We especially got to know Sonny--heâ€™s the man to see when in Houston. He recommended 3 restaurants to us and they were all outstanding. I had the best steak Iâ€™ve ever had and Sonny pointed the way! He drove the shuttle van and took us where we need to go. Our other colleagues stayed at the Hilton, Hyatt, and Crowne Plaza. Little â€™ole Best Western had them all beat!!! Our stay cost about 1/3 less and we had all the great perks!! One colleague commented that her bottled water was $3.50 at the Hilton. I cannot rave enough about this hotel. I will be returning to Houston for another conference in the future and will stay at the Best Western.',239853,00000000023),
(00094106543,'2011-01-23','January',2011,0,'F',5,5,4,5,5,3,'Nice','Stayed in a Grande King which is a good, comfortable size. Nice bathroom, and probably the BEST king bed Iâ€™ve slept in at any hotel of recent memory. Only direct complaint is the $25-ish overnight valet parking charge, which seems crazy. Beware that this hotel is in a dead zone for [AT&T] cell service. Couldnâ€™t keep a call with signal hovering between 0-1 bars. Not the hotelâ€™s fault, I lose calls always driving this stretch of Main/San Jacinto. I checked in very late and had to leave very early so I didnâ€™t get to really enjoy the accomodation as much as I would have liked. But I look forward to my next stay there. Read somewhere the hotel allows pets which I donâ€™t get, but I didnâ€™t see any.',641273,00000000090),
(00094106876,'2011-01-23','January',2011,1,'F',4,3,4,4,4,3,'Good value but itâ€™s time for some upgraded am','Great re-use of an early-century bank building (giant vault door behind the check-in counter!). Room was a good size and a great bathroom with nice jet tub. The two disappointments were the CRT/not-flat-panel TV, and the spongy bed with average sheeting. I think itâ€™s time for the hotel to invest in these upgrades as their peers have already done. Nice location with lots of restaurant options in walking distance. This is also another downtown hotel with no option but for valet parking and the $25-ish charge seems unnecessarily high. I noticed the glass shelf in the bathroom hadnâ€™t been dusted recently either.',283873,00000000090),
(00094597017,'2011-01-27','November',2010,0,'F',5,5,5,4,5,3,'Clean and comfortable; would definitely stay ','Very nice full service hotel. Rooms are very clean and comfortable. Good location next to shopping haven in Houston. If you are familiar with the Marriott brand, this hotel will not disappoint.',99010,00000000028),
(00094744794,'2011-01-28','January',2011,0,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'An Excellent HGI Property','As always, making my reservation took less than 3 minutes using the Hilton website. The hotel is located just off a major freeway/frontage road. The hotel offers plenty of convenient and free parking. I was greeted with a smile, welcomed by name, and my check-in took less than a minute. The hotel itself is very clean and well-maintained. The hotel caters to business travelers and at least in the early evening the lobby/bar area is fairly noisy. My room was on the sixth floor and was also very clean, with a spotless duvet and a very comfortable bed. I am a long-time Hilton Diamond HHonors member, and virtually all of my domestic hotel stays are at HGI properties for reasons (as in this case) include: free and convenient parking, free high-speed internet, a free and well-equipped business center, a clean indoor pool and a free and well-equipped fitness center, and a restaurant offering good food at reasonable prices. If you like to workout, I recommend that you get to the fitness center as early as you can because the place fills up fast.  The property, its staff, my room, and all of the usual HGI amenities made for a very comfortable and enjoyable stay. I recommend this property to you.',1158926,00000000077),
(00094748006,'2011-01-28','January',2011,0,'F',3,4,5,3,2,3,'Very convenient to Airport - But Expensive','As always, making my reservation took less than 3 minutes using the Hilton website. The hotel is located just a couple of minutes from the Austin airport and itâ€™s that location that is the best (and possibly only) thing that recommends this hotel. On the other hand, the Hilton Garden Inn and Hilton in downtown Austin (I checked them both out as they are located near each other) would have been unaccetpable as there were homeless people wandering around both of the downtown hotels and their location next to the freeway placed them in a congested, noisy, and fairly unattractive location. So, it was the Airport Hilton for me. The hotel is maybe a 15 minute drive from downtown. As has sadly been the trend with Hiltons over the last few years, staying at this hotel involves being nickled and dimed from the minute you arrive. Youâ€™ll pay to park, whether using the valet parking or self-parking. Similarly, in-room internet and/or internet in the business center is charged for.  The front desk staff was slow, and appeared confused - initially I was checked into and given a key for a room reserved for some other guest. Total check-in time was about 10 minutes, way too long given that I was the only person checking in at the time. The hotel itself is in the shape of a drum, with a large circular atrium. There are two rings of rooms, one with â€™â€™viewsâ€™â€™ only of the atrium, while the other ring has rooms that have outside views (either of a freeway or the airport). My room was on the fourth floor (top floor) and was clean with a duvet and a very comfortable matress for bedding. HVAC was quite powerful and made cooling off the room fast and easy. This hotel offers a large and well-equipped fitness center. Water pressure from the shower was anemic and it took a long time to get the soap off given the trickle of water the shower produced. Check-out the next morning was again a slow process (the night auditor rather than a front desk person) but due to the location of the hotel, I was at the airport in less than five minutes. Overall, what you are paying for at this Hilton property is location and the fact that the hotel is literally on the grounds of the airport. Otherwise, I found this hotel to be expensive for the product (room) offered, exacerbated by the additional charges for parking and internet access that are free at other Hilton brands like the Hilton Garden Inns.  I can recommend this property, but itâ€™s a close call, with my recommendation based almost entirely on the hotelâ€™s location adjacent to the airport.',223686,00000000077),
(00094777528,'2011-01-28','January',2011,0,'F',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'No thanks.','This hotel used to be okay years ago, but on my last stay I crossed it off my list. Bedspread was stained and seemed dirty. Pillows STANK, and thatâ€™s one of my hotel pet peeves is old, stinky pillows. The rest of the room was okay, but I need restful sleep when Iâ€™m traveling on business...and sleeping in a dirty stinky bed doesnâ€™t do it.',223151,00000000099),
(00095320180,'2011-02-02','January',2011,2,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'Luxurious accommodations, personal service an','My daughter and I spent last weekend at The Sherry-Netherland, and were immediately impressed with the warm welcome at the front desk and the handwritten welcome note in our room. The staff made us feel at home, from the elevator operators who knew our floor, to the doormen who always greeted us so graciously. Our suite was lovely, appointed with beautiful furnishings in soft colors, and the bedding was so comfortable, it was like sleeping on a cloud! The location of the hotel could not be better, right on Fifth Ave at 59th St, overlooking the main entrance to Central Park. The highly acclaimed restaurant, Harry Cipriani, is there to be enjoyed by hotel guests as well as New Yorkers in the know. We think The Sherry-Netherland is a true gem, and give it the highest marks for luxury, service and location in New York City!!!!',93559,00000000097),
(00095331082,'2011-02-02','February',2011,0,'F',4,5,4,4,5,4,'Good, solid, comfortable hotel for the busine','Westin property attached to the Galleria shopping mall, offering a wide array of shopping and dining options. Sister property to the Westin Oaks, but definitely the one of the two to stay at if you are considering the Westin. Spacious and clean rooms, generally very comfortable and new furniture. Friendly, prompt, and attentive staff. Floor to ceiling windows allow for a lot of light. Free parking close to the hotel entrance.',99114,00000000091),
(00095808053,'2011-02-07','January',2011,1,'F',4,5,5,5,4,3,'Very nice hotel','The view from this hotel goes without saying given its geometry and relative height. The floor to ceiling windows provide a great view of the city and the room is very well laid out. As with all Westin hotels, the room is tastefully simple and the staff is exceptionally friendly.',100570,00000000102),
(00096330541,'2011-02-12','February',2011,0,'F',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Great Location, It is a Westin; say no more','It is hard to beat the location of this hotel. Free parking in the Galleria mall, direct access to the Mall, and many great restaurants in close proximity. The hotel is not new, but they have done a reasonable job of updating it; the rooms are large and furnishings more to my taste than most hotels.',99114,00000000086),
(00096527787,'2011-02-13','January',2011,2,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'One of The Best Hotel Experiences of My Life','If I were to run a hotel, Iâ€™d do it the way itâ€™s done by the staff of The Sherry-Netherland. Iâ€™d been told by a friend of the superior staff, rooms, service, historical ambiance, still I knew there was no such place left in the U.S. Boy, was I wrong.  The building is comprised mainly of apartments, lending it an air of quiet elegance, not at all dreary like some historic hotels. It faces the SE corner of Central Park, convenient for shopping and hopping on local transportation. The rooms are cheerful and immaculate, tastefully appointed with modern conveniences. As a side note, the park was too icy to run in during my stay; I discovered the Sherry has one of the best fitness rooms Iâ€™ve ever visited at a hotel! Prices are steep, but what isnâ€™t in the city? I canâ€™t wait to be able to come back to The Sherry!',93559,00000000089),
(00096638290,'2011-02-14','February',2011,2,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'Great Hotel and perfect staff','I spent the weekend at the hotel and the service was perfect. The room was great and the staff was awesome as always. This is my favorite hotel in New York.',93559,00000000088),
(00097499462,'2011-02-21','February',2011,0,'F',5,4,5,5,5,5,'BIG LUXURY ROOM','This hotel has an excellent location (faces Central Park South) 1/2 block to a yellow subway station, big luxury junior suite, nice TV, amenities and linens. Nice room service (expensive, but good). Any way there is a convenience store just in the corner. The only complaint: No good wi.fi signal in the room. Everything else is just fine.',455186,00000000061),
(00097904919,'2011-02-24','February',2011,1,'F',5,5,3,4,5,5,'Lovely hidden gem','I love this simple hotel! Sparkling clean with extrodinarily comfortable beds tucked into spacious rooms.  It clings to the outskirts of down town and offers free shuttles for the out and about. The staff is efficient and carrying...they fussed more than I did when I thought I lost my phone.   The entire hotel is a non-smoking oasis.',239853,00000000020),
(00098334761,'2011-02-28','February',2011,2,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'One of the best Hilton properties Iâ€™ve ever s','This Hampton Inn is located in a newer commercial area with excellent access to the nearby interstate. It is located within a cluster of other new hotels/motels. In fact, in addition to this Hampton, you will also find a brand new Hilton Garden Inn and a new Hilton within this cluster. I normally stay at HGI properties, but based on the Tripadvisor reviews I rolled the dice and stayed here - and I was happy I did. This Hampton lived up to and/or exceeded the reviews and my own expectations. I had a â€™â€™junior suiteâ€™â€™ on the 5th floor of this new 6 floor hotel. I recommend you pay the small additional amount for the huge space and comfort the junior suites offer. I found it to be an excellent value. There is plenty of free and convenient parking. The hotel is set back from roads and well away from the freeway, so the setting is very quiet. Check-in took less than a minute and the two guys on the front desk were friendly and yet professional. The main floor offers a free business center, guest laundry, and fitness center, along with an area where the hotel offers a free breakfast. All common areas were â€™â€™like newâ€™â€™. My own room was clean and well maintained. What I especially liked was the work desk chair which, unlike the hard-as-a-rock chairs in HGI properties, was a very comfortable and nicely padded chair. The bathroom was clean and well stocked. My bedding (duvet) was spotless and comfortable and provided a great nightâ€™s sleep. The small coffee/sink area was similarly spotless and what I liked was that Hampton offers coffee/water cups that are single-use and sealed in plastic bags - there is no wondering whether housekeeping really cleaned/replaced the glasses/coffee cups. The rooms also feature a small fridge, a microwave, and a large HD flat panel TV. While the location is not in the central/core of Columbus, and is perhaps 15 - 20 minutes from the airport, I found the location to be perfect for my needs. And in all respects, this Hampton Inn was everything and more that previous reviewers have mentioned as positives. I have been staying at Hilton properties for nearly 35 years and I am a long-standing Diamond HHonors member. I can honestly say that this Hampton ranks at or near the top among all of the Hilton-branded properties Iâ€™ve stayed at. I strongly recommend this hotel to you!',878115,00000000077),
(00099064403,'2011-03-05','February',2011,1,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'Live Like a New Yorker','OK, so most of us canâ€™t afford to be upper east-siders. But we can stay at the Sherry to see what the big deal is. And, it is a big deal. Walking distance to Broadway, the Lincoln Center and the main art museums. (donâ€™t miss the Whitney!), as well as the many wonderful restaurants. Then, the hotel itself is no hotel. It is a residence. The staff is as professional as they come. We stayed for several days and lost the feeling of being yokels from Virginia because we were treated as residents. The rooms are exquisitely appointed and larger than the NYC norm. Ciprianiâ€™s is the attached restaurant and has great service and excellent food, which came with a discount, since we were residents â€¦ er â€¦ hotel guests. We try to get to the Apple at least once a year and traditionally select the Sherry. Occasionally we experiment with other venues such as the Plaza. But we have always happily returned to â€œourâ€ place. The Sherry. Weâ€™d give it six stars, if we could.',93559,00000000081),
(00099473062,'2011-03-08','March',2011,1,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'FANTASTIC!','What a superb place to stay in NYC! Gorgeous rooms, friendly and helpful staff, perfect location. Totally delightful.',93559,00000000080),
(00099525704,'2011-03-09','March',2011,0,'F',4,4,5,5,4,5,'Highly functional, very quiet, a good deal al','The Pearl NYC is an excellent deal for the leisure traveler. Itâ€™s new and everything works as it should. The Pearl offers an outstanding location on 49th Street only a few steps from Times Square. The style is crisp and utilitarian but lacking in any real aesthetic rationale.  The breakfast is nothing to write home about, but if you like bread stuffs Iâ€™m sure you can get filled up before leaving the hotel in the morning. The rooms are large by NYC or European standards, the baths are mostly marble with nice enclosed showers. The bath room amenities are quite good and towels plentiful and quite thick. The windows are sound proofed (some occasional street sounds are unavoidable in NYC I believe) and there is no sound transfer between rooms or from the hallwalls. This is a botique hotel but the services are quite good. We got help with our bags, there is limited room service, a small but modern fitness room, and a free mornning newspaper available from the front desk. My only small complaint was that the room lighting is quite dim and the bed side lamps only have 57 Watt bulbs; probably not strong enough for most readers.  We would stay here again, especially for the pittance we paid for our three night stay!',1888977,00000000073),
(00099534181,'2011-03-09','March',2011,0,'F',3,3,4,2,4,2,'Typical Embassy Suites: getting rundown','This hotel seems to reflect the typical state of Embassy Suites these days: neglected and rundown. This hotel is in a great location, and I have no trouble finding parking in the surface lot. The lobby is fine. The rooms, however, are showing their age. The furniture in the â€™â€™living roomâ€™â€™ part of the suite were elevated on ugly wood blocks! The bed had that lopsided thing going on, where it slants downward on the side that everyone sits down on. The TV had about half the channels that were fuzzy. The sofa was so poorly built and so worn, that if you sat down in the middle of it the the cushions popped up on either side of you. This place is okay if you arenâ€™t too picky about the things I mentioned, but I sure wouldnâ€™t pay over $160/night for this hotel.',223145,00000000099),
(00099712780,'2011-03-10','March',2011,0,'F',5,4,4,4,5,4,'Always a pleasure!','The staff is always focused on taking care of itâ€™s clients. We had a meeting at this location for two days and the food was better than anticipated. Iâ€™m sure we will be back in the near future!!',1158926,00000000069),
(00100374562,'2011-03-16','March',2011,0,'F',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Miserable','Never again will I stay here--and I travel for business to Houston every week. The culprit? The window-unit Air Conditioner--probably one of the worst Iâ€™ve ever experienced. Iâ€™m very tolerant of noise, because I sleep like a log--but this one literally jolted me out of my sleep when it starts up. Even worse is that when it runs, it literally vibrates the room and the air in the room, while parts inside continue to rattle the entire time.  The toilet makes a high-pitched whistle/whine for about 5 minutes after being flushed.  I just wonder how much longer travelers are going to willing to put up with these crappy window air conditioners that are used by these mid-level hotels. Most of them are loud, but the one here at this hotel is literally unbearable. Iâ€™ll be asking to either change rooms, or Iâ€™ll be checking out early-thatâ€™s how bad it is.',223154,00000000099),
(00100805992,'2011-03-20','February',2011,0,'F',3,3,5,3,4,5,'Smelly lobby','The lobby of the hotel smelled from â€™â€™essential oilsâ€™â€™ air freshener. The chemicals from this air freshener made me very ill and I would not recommend anyone with allergies or chemical sensitivities breathing in the toxic fumes.',114134,00000000070),
(00101054092,'2011-03-21','March',2011,2,'F',5,5,4,5,5,5,'The Best Value Choice in Houston','I stood 4 nights at this hotel with my mother (shopping trip). Before booking a room for four nights at the Best Western Downtown Inn and Suites, I read some reviews about this and other hotels on the downtown zone (Doubletree, Marriot Courtyard, etc.) and Iâ€™m glad to say that all of the good comments that were written about BW are true. The hotel is located right oustide the Houston downtown, but outside doesnâ€™t mean far. The few times I decided to walk to the downtown, a 15-minutes walk took me to the heart of it. If you arenâ€™t a walkiing person, the shuttle of the hotel will take you anywhere within the downtown area or even to the midtown if the distance isnâ€™t too far.  The rooms are clean, spacious and very well equipped with an iron, a coffee maker, the basic bathroom amenities, satellital TV and as many bottles of water as you can drink. It also has a microwave and a small fridge, which makes your stay even more comfortable. Vending machines are avaiable to get microwave food and sodas whenever you want. The best of the hotel is the staff: Jo, the front-desk lady is just lovely and helpful. Sonny (the multi-task guy of the business) is always ready to give you a ride on the shuttle or to recommend you the hot spots to hang out at night. There is a third front-desk guy called Don, that kindly took us to a Walgreenâ€™s like 20 blocks away from the hotel in his own car, as the shuttle only works from Monday to Friday. That was something nice I didnâ€™t expect. The breakfast is simple but effective: waffles, sweet bread, cereal, milk, coffee, eggs, sausages and bacon. They serve the same breakfast everyday, so try to â€™â€™rotateâ€™â€™ your choices if you are staying more than one night and you donâ€™t like to have the same everyday. The hotel is totally non-smoking. If you are a nicotine addict, DONâ€™T DO IT INSIDE the rooms. During our stay, we saw two guys being kindly kicked out of the hotel after paying a $ 250.00 fine for smoking inside. The only thing I didnâ€™t like were the pillows. They were too large and squishy and itâ€™s the only kind of pillows they have, so if you are a â€™â€™firmâ€™â€™ pillows user like me, you will have to bring yours.  In conclusion, if I ever visit Houston again, I will stay here for sure.',239853,00000000019),
(00101592674,'2011-03-26','December',2010,3,'F',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'fun, elegant and personal','stayed at the sherry for 3 nights whilst in new york, which is one of my favourite cities in the world. the staff there are the best thing about it.... warm and helpful, but never intruding. the rooms are beautifully appointed without trying too hard, with a botanical theme. because iâ€™m not fond of large impersonal lobbies, i was really pleased arriving at the sherry despite the bustle outside its entrance. it felt like SUCH a privilege every time i walked through that revolving door. although i would have preferred a slightly quieter address further into the upper east side, there is something to be said for its proximity to bergdorf goodman :P  although we didnâ€™t make use of the room service, i believe many good things have been said about its neighbour Harry cipriani. iâ€™m always charmed by any establishment that offers free drinks in its minibar - whilst not the type to drink many of them in the first place, it just seems so much less â€™commercialâ€™ this way... honestly, whoâ€™s going to drink 20 cans of coke from the minibar, even if they were free?  so... the sherry might suit someone like me, who prefers their hotels thoughtful, beautiful and intimate.',93559,00000000079),
(00101621540,'2011-03-26','December',2010,0,'F',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'really happy with our experience here','stayed here for several days during a conference with my now-husband... whilst the hotel might not look that impressive as you go out of the taxi, there was plenty i liked about it. it was cozy, and despite having a large number of guests, the staff are always helpful and friendly (no frazzled faces whilst we were there!). the rooms themselves are indeed homely, clean and large, and i found it particularly helpful that there were laundry facilities within the hotel that were easy to use.  breakfasts were delicious, and i always appreciated being able to make a hot chocolate and bring it up to my room any time of day.  the location is fantastic, being in close proximity to the magnificent mile and several great restaurants (we tried lawrys and a crab place just around the corner..? forgot the name now). the doormen were always friendly and had a smile despite the freezing temperatures, poor things. will be staying here again for future conferences in chicago!',90959,00000000079),
(00101646678,'2011-03-26','March',2011,0,'F',3,3,5,3,1,3,'A Tired Airport Hotel That Only Has Its Locat','I am recommending this hotel solely on the basis of its location so close to LAX. If you are a Hilton HHonors member, there are other, likely better Hilton-brand options to consider (like the Embassy Suites North or the Hilton Garden Inn - Iâ€™ve stayed at both hotels and they are good options). If you are not tied to the Hilton family of hotels, there are probably much better options located close to the hotel. Getting to the hotel from LAX is via shuttle bus. The hotel no longer operates its own shuttle, but uses a contractor. Shuttles serve more than one hotel. The buses are old, loud, and uncomfortable. The shuttle makes its first stop at the Hilton; on the way to the airport, you will make at least one stop at another hotel. Keep this in mind when planning out how long it will take you to get back to the airport. When the shuttle arrives at the hotel, itâ€™s a race to the checkin counter at the back of the hotel. If youâ€™re slow, you will wait to check in. My checkin took about 10 minutes and was handled in a competent if not particularly welcoming manner. This Hilton is tired. When was the last time you had a room with an old-style television with a picture tube? The hotel hasnâ€™t upgraded to flat panel televisions. Common areas are worn down. My room was dark and small, with what felt like a very low ceiling. The walls were scuffed, wall paper was peeling away, and the bathroom was cramped and not particularly clean. The roomâ€™s HVAC system was anemic and the construction of the building allowed noise (jets taking off) into the room, making sleep difficult. My bottom line is that this hotel is only acceptable when transiting LAX (which I was doing) and solely on the basis of its location so close to LAX. In any event, the hotelâ€™s owners need to invest in refurbishing/updating this property. The Hilton LAX has a lot of potential; itâ€™s sad that it doesnâ€™t come close to meeting that potential.',84167,00000000077),
(00101844583,'2011-03-28','March',2011,0,'F',4,4,5,3,5,5,'Great locations and good value','My husband and I stayed there for one night and the location and service are great. It is a very old hotel and they have not updated many things that need attention, like the carpeting and the kitchen areas. Nevertheless, it is a great find. The only suggestion I have is that the check in area and breakfast room have very pungent flowers that filled the air with a very sweet smell. Flowers do not bother me, but the smell of these were overwhelming.',84082,00000000070),
(00102630021,'2011-04-03','March',2011,0,'F',2,2,1,2,1,2,'The worst hotel stay I have had in years','Let me start by saying something nice. The front desk manager Lolita was a pleasure to get to know. She always had a huge smile on her face and teased me right back when I teased her; however, she needed help on the weekend we stayed. On to my complaints: 1. Our room was never cleaned or refreshed. I had two daughters with me for a soccer tournament, and we returned at around 9 pm on Saturday night from a long day of soccer. We were worn out and needed to eat something and get the kids into bed. Upon arrival, we decided to eat something in the restaurant/bar area. The food was really good, but it took forever. Every time I walked through the lobby area, there was a check in line that stretched from the front desk literally out the front door. Poor Lolita was the only person there to check all of these people in. I am not kidding. the line was there from the time we entered till the time we finally went to bed.  2. Anyway, we finally got to our room, and the key didnâ€™t work. I knew I was going to have to go and stand in that line, and I was not happy. I went and stood in the line for 15 minutes. Lolita was apologetic and gave us new keys.  3. When we finally got into our room sometime around 10:30, we arrived only to find that the room had never been cleaned. All of our towels were dirty from the morning before, and my kids and I desperately needed a shower. I called housekeeping...no answer. I think I left a message, but it has been a while. Anyway, I finally called Lolita. I told her that we desperately needed towels. I asked if I could come down and get some. She said that she would have someone bring them. My kids showered and used dirty towels. The clean towels never came.  4. The next morning upon checkout, I let the front desk manager know of our experience the night before. His response was that it was the weekend, and they only have 1/2 of the usual staff. I was stunned and nicely told him that was not an acceptable excuse.  5. One last item, the bathrooms are tiny. I have never seen a smaller commode. I am not a huge person, and I could not sit on the seat without my feces landing on the commode seat. I commented on this to another member of our party who stayed, and they laughed about having the exact same experience.  6. Finally, there was a seedy group of people hanging around the parking lot and lobby of this hotel. I am pretty sure there were prostitutes turning tricks in the bar area the night we were there. No, I am not joking. It is not a very friendly hotel for kids.  This hotel does not deserve a 3 star rating. I give it a 2 on a good day.',98964,00000000066),
(00102758797,'2011-04-04','April',2011,0,'F',4,5,3,4,4,4,'Good hotel if location to Houston isnâ€™t impor','We selected this hotel over hotels closer to Houston because of its high rating in Trip Advisor. I was a little disappointed and wish I had gone with a hotel closer to the city. Itâ€™s not that itâ€™s a bad hotel, it isnâ€™t. It just donesnâ€™t deserve being the #6 best hotel in Houston. From my standards, itâ€™s a very good hotel, just what you would expect from a Hampton or a Garden Inn, but itâ€™s not an outstanding hotel. On the downside, the service is spotty. Some staff are increadibly helpful while others are not. For example, wanting a cup of coffee around 3 pm on a Sunday afternoon we discovered it was cold. When we told the front desk about it, their reply was that we would have to wait a couple of hours until the new shift came on duty. What?! Room service was also slow on some days. We had to wait until 5:30 pm on a Sunday to get a maid to make up our room. On the upside, the breakfast is very nice at a cost of $10 per person. There are cookies in the lobby in the afternoon. The wireless Internet and parking is free. The exercise room is minimal but acceptable. The rooms were clean, comfortable, and quiet which is what is more important than a hot cup of coffee on a Sunday afternoon.',1158926,00000000067),
(00102821363,'2011-04-04','March',2011,1,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'best location, amazing views','Best location on the park, amazing views, staff lovely, made me feel welcome, rooms are airy light and beautifully appointed. I spend only 2 days here before moving on to another place to stay. Great start to my New York visit, excellent breakfast and room service. Thank you to everyone at the Sherry!',93559,00000000078),
(00102853553,'2011-04-04','March',2011,0,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'Top Notch Customer Service','I recently booked a room at this Hilton for just the day, as I was in town for business. The staff was so accommodating and friendly, both before and during the stay. They expected me by name and made me welcome. They were polite and helpful. The hotel was very nice, but I have to say I was most impressed with the hospitality of the staff. They were just outstanding!! I will definitely be recommending this hotel to everyone I know! I was raving about the hotel to everyone I knew as soon as I stepped out the door.',108038,00000000015),
(00103039485,'2011-04-06','March',2011,0,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'absolutely lovely','Stayed here in March for a week and was treated like a member of the family, all staff were warm, welcoming and friendly. Special mention of Lovely Dutch girl in the Pembrooke room and the fabulous doorman, sorry dont remember their name, but they made me feel welcome everytime i stepped out and in.. Very good room facilities, comfortable bed, mini bar is really high standard and has got excellent choice, room service and dinner at posthouse all brilliant. Location was wonderful, as it felt safe, and quiet and residential , as if I was coming home every night! Thank you everyone at the Lowell, i will definately recommend and come back!',93585,00000000078),
(00103213150,'2011-04-07','April',2011,2,'F',5,5,4,5,5,5,'Outstanding Service','My buddy and I stayed at the Best Western during the Final Four. Itâ€™s a couple of blocks from downtown Houston. However, the location turned out to be ideal as mid-town is also a couple of blocks in a different direction and it has a terrific collection of bars and restaurants. Sonny who works at the front desk will be happy to drive you to any of them. The free breakfast was outstanding. Jo (who really runs the place) could not have been a better host and made sure that all of our needs were met. They probably donâ€™t pay her enough given that she goes out of her way to make sure the guests are happy. Bottom line: the hotel met our needs',239853,00000000018),
(00103783849,'2011-04-12','April',2011,0,'F',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wow! Best Place EVER!!','We have stayed at many, many four star hotels, but our recent stay at this Embassy Suites eclipses just about all of them. From the moment we pulled into valet, we were treated with friendliness, helpful attitudes, top notch customer service from every employee we met. Not only were our questions answered, the recommendation for dinner and directions to where we needed to go were spot on and accurate. I cannot recommend this place highly enough. Even the snacks at the managerâ€™s reception were a notch above normal, with fresh veggies and hummus dip, tables quickly cleared and bar service that was speedy and friendly. Love this place and canâ€™t wait to go back!!!',1859056,00000000029),
(00103830263,'2011-04-12','April',2011,0,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'This is a great hotel','In for yet another soccer tournament. We really enjoyed our stay. Everything was so clean and neat. There was a warm smell of cookies or vanilla in the lobby that made it feel welcoming. Our room was spacious, and the beds were very comfortable. The front desk staff was friendly and accommodating. I highly recommend this hotel. Conveniently located just off of I-10.',1158926,00000000066),
(00103949658,'2011-04-13','May',2010,0,'F',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rooftop + Bath Products = Joy','I stayed in my own room as did my colleagues on a business trip in May 2010. This was slightly after the change from being a boutique hotel (The Ivy) to a Hyatt property. It did not feel like a mainstram hotel at all, it was definitely unique in all aspects. I stayed for a about 4 or 5 nights and I think that every day I discovered a new nook or cranny.  The bath products then, and hopefully they still are, amazing. I could create a small stockpile if I wanted to. They had wonderfully smelling Korres products. I still stop at Sephora and sniff the Aloe shampoo and it brings me back great memories from my week at Andaz.  I actually worked on the rooftop for a few hours on two different days. I just tucked myself into a cabana and it was quite peaceful, there were even outlets in there. The weather in May was not at summer temperatures yet, but my Portland, Oregon body needed some rays and warmth. The pool was pretty empty during the day. of course at night the rooftop turns into a hip nightspot (that was fun to experience too). Awesome restaurant on the roof. Fun dancing in the basement at night. Interesting wine bar on the ground level.  I did not try the main restaurant, so I cannot review. I loved the space in the room, the design was fun and young but wasnâ€™t over the top. I didnâ€™t have a room with a stripper pole in it as I was there for work. But I think you can request that if you so choose.',625335,00000000063),
(00103972505,'2011-04-13','April',2011,1,'F',3,3,5,4,4,3,'Hope you love traffic noise!! (Stay at the We','Only a 1-night stay at this Westin property and glad for it. The Westin Galleria, the sister property on the other side of The Galleria where Iâ€™ve stayed the last two trips, doesnâ€™t front Westheimer and therefore doesnâ€™t offer an unbelievable amount of road noise coming through the windows, especially from the high number of racing bikes racing down Westheimer. I arrived into the lobby to check in around 7pm and was greeted with an overpowering varnish/paint smell there, then at the 8th floor was greeted with a smell most akin to a skunk. Then once I settled into the room, I became aware that the TV was competing against the Westheimer noise. If I were not staying but one night (leaving early in the morning) Iâ€™d absolutely be asking to move rooms. Iâ€™ve advised my corporate travel agent to remove this from my list of places to stay.',99135,00000000090),
(00103973114,'2011-04-14','April',2011,0,'F',4,4,4,2,4,3,'Good option','I am satisfied with this blind pick for a good full-service, IAH-convenient hotel and was able to secure a decent rate. Architecture is dated â€™80s, and studio-style roomsâ€™ windows into the corridor struck me as peculiar, as well as having flat screen HDTVs without HD-quality picture (old LodgeNet interface not yet upgraded). But hotel lobby is shared with an office building which apparently gives it enough traffic for a full Starbucks kiosk which was a nice alternative to the full restaurant option which I did not try but looked good. Clean. Staff is friendly. But isnâ€™t it time for free internet?',99137,00000000090),
(00104594481,'2011-04-19','April',2011,1,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'What a great experience!!','I had to make a visit to Houston to see my brother who had a stroke. I came on a red eye trip 7am - so I was very tired. Jo ( front desk lady) let us check in early and let us get some breakfast. The rooms were so spacious. The hotel made us feel right at home. We will be back!!',239853,00000000014),
(00105044889,'2011-04-22','April',2011,0,'F',4,5,4,4,5,4,'Very nice, rooms are too hot though','I had a very nice 3-night stay here while on a business trip. Self-parking in the garage is convenient but expensive. The food is INCREDIBLE--room service was fantastic. Turndown service is nice. Bed was very comfortable altho they donâ€™t use the fitted bottom sheet yet, which means when you pull back the top sheet at night to get in bed, the bottom sheets pulls out and you have to retuck it.  The only quibble I have with this hotel is the room temperature. It was too hot for my tastes. The hotel uses regular light bulbs, so the bathroom in particular, while well-lit, was hot. Itâ€™s a catch-22 with hotel air conditioning: central air is quiet but doesnâ€™t get cool enough; room units are extremely noisy but get the room nice and cold.  All in all I would stay here again. Excellent service, fantastic food, nice bed.',99060,00000000099),
(00105642992,'2011-04-26','April',2011,0,'F',5,5,5,5,5,3,'Such nice southern hospitality!','We booked here because they were able to offer connecting rooms and the location was good for visiting family. We arrived at 10pm and there were no connecting rooms, (we could have called ahead to confirm but did not). The front desk staff worked together to come up with a plan to accommodate our family and after the first night we switched one of the rooms which worked fine. They were so polite and helpful. In fact, EVERYONE working at the hotel was unbelievably hospitable....a very well trained staff! Price seemed low coming from Calif but we found out that other similar hotels in the area were less expensive. Still, no complaints. Rooms were quiet, large, comfortable and clean and staff was amazing so it was money well spent!',1158926,00000000065),
(00106130640,'2011-04-29','April',2011,3,'F',4,5,5,5,5,4,'Top service, old world charm and reasonable p','If you like old world charm and the best location in NYC, this is the hotel for you. Situated in New Yorkâ€™s most outstanding street corner, the hotel offers great rooms, a coziness that only an hotel with 50 rooms can provide, a staff that greets you with a smile and an atmosphere similar to New Yorkâ€™s top tier hotels. Prices are reasonable for New Yorkâ€™s standards and rooms are big, very well decorated and with all the amenities that youâ€™ d expect from a five star hotel. The only problem was the noise from the courtyard, because of the air conditioning units that work all day and night. A second minor problem is that you have to wait a couple minutes for the hot water in the shower, because - I suppose - plumbing is tired. But besides that, I recommend this hotel to those who would like to stay confortably in New Yorkâ€™s best address and in a landmark building that has been kept in pristine condition.',93559,00000000075),
(00108295155,'2011-05-15','May',2011,1,'F',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'The manhattan hotel','Itâ€™s not the typical hotel with a big lobby. However if you want a quiet but upscale hotel this is it. You are welcome from the minute you step in until you leave. The staff pro guest ratio is very low so I never waited in line for any service. The staff were very friendly with my kids. Location was perfect as it was in a safe area to walk around, food choices are aplenty in the area. Beside subway and bus stops. Service was impeccable',93559,00000000074),
(00108296200,'2011-05-15','May',2011,0,'F',4,5,5,4,4,3,'Heart of frisco','Choice between this and hotel near pier. This was better location as it was in the heart of city. You could literally walk to anywhere. Hotel was a real hotel with all amenities. Security was impeccably good. Rooms were really good, clean and new. Near union square, market St and powell. Great for families as youâ€™ll feel secure. Walking to all shops highend , mid and low. Lovely base ca,p when visiting the city.  Only negative was expensive parking and no free valet for short checkins. Wifi Internet free only in lobby.',81295,00000000074),
(00109134104,'2011-05-20','May',2011,2,'F',5,5,5,5,5,5,'So mellow I nearly couldnâ€™t, almost, wake up ','The Sherry Netherland functions so smoothly it could almost put you to sleep. This is not neccessary a good or bad thing. That will depend on whether youâ€™re looking for excitement, or predicability. My wife and I like both equally, both canâ€™t afford the grand a night it costs. For us there is the Sherry Netherland. Perfectly located; historical, friendly, intimate, cumfy, and quiet. Five stars all around, but especially for value!',93559,00000000073),
(00110931598,'2011-06-01','May',2011,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Wedding Reception ROCKED!','Our son and new daughter in law had their wedding reception here. It not only met expectations, but exceeded our expectations. The event planner and restaurant manager were on site for the entire event making sure everything ran smoothly. There was plenty of waitstaff, the food was amazing and the event was truly magical. Truly lived up to the Hilton name.',1158926,00000000064),
(00111590347,'2011-06-05','May',2011,0,'F',4,4,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Exactly as we expected.','Stayed there overnight. When I first pulled up, the property looked a little old, but it was very clean. Upon entering, it was clear to me that they had worked hard to update the lobby and decor. The rooms were perfectly clean. It looked like the rooms had been recently updated. The bathroom and t.v. had been renovated. The bathroom was average size. Beds were very comfortable. They were actually renovating the hall we were staying in, but they were not actually working at the time. The hall was just torn up a bit where they are making changes. It was a very quiet hotel with not alot of traffic, etc. Front desk staff was very friendly and helpful. Got a good price through Priceline.com. Would stay at this hotel again.',526841,00000000066),
(00111591814,'2011-06-05','June',2011,2,'F',4,5,NULL,NULL,5,3,'1st time to stay and liked it.','Pricelined this hotel on a very busy weekend of soccer in the area. The outside is very neat and clean. Plenty of parking space. Located close to Hwy 249 and Willowbrook Mall. Easy access from roadway. Lobby area very clean and modern. Front desk personnel very friendly and helpful. Willing to kid a little with me. I liked that. Chandra was really alot of fun. The room was spacious and comfortable. All amenities worked. T.V. did not have alot of choices, but we werenâ€™t in the room that much. So it didnâ€™t matter much. The free breakfast was really good with lots of seating opportunities. Did not feel crowded. My daughter loved being able to get the hot chocolate in the serving area. Only negative is I got stuck in one of the elevators that stopped working. I was not there long, and I noticed they had someone working on it later that day. It was out of service for most of our stay, but it did not keep us from getting to and from our room because there is a 2nd elevator. The pool was nice and clean. Over all it was a good stay. The price was a little high even for priceline, but I think that is because there were so many soccer tournaments in the area on that weekend.',223193,00000000066),
(00111850715,'2011-06-06','March',2011,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Let me count the ways I adore you, HGI-Energy','I have stayed at this hotel numerous times in Houston when I come to town to visit my clients in the Energy Corridor. I love the convenient location and the staff are great too. Iâ€™ve stayed at countless Hilton properties and this one is one of my go-toâ€™s and favorites. This hotel is a gem in the HGI crown! Let me count the ways I love this place:  - (Insert oil company name here) is just minutes away!  - Thereâ€™s a Kinkoâ€™s next door!  - I donâ€™t have to get on the freeway to get to my meetings!  - There are tons of restaurant options nearby (sushi, Mexican, BBQ, etc)! - I am always greeted as a return customer, and theyâ€™ve upgraded my rooms a few times! This hotel has great hospitality and I think it is a no brainer if youâ€™re going here for business. The staff are great and know what they are doing.  One tip though - book well in advance, because this HGIâ€™s awesomeness is known around town to energy corridor business travelers, this HGI is often booked to capacity. Iâ€™ve had to pull the Hilton strings more than once to make a reservation when theyâ€™ve appeared to be sold out. Now you have a tip to outsmart everyone to get your room here, too.',1158926,00000000063),
(00112657146,'2011-06-10','May',2011,0,'F',4,4,4,4,4,4,'My regular H-town hotel','I travel to Houston almost every week on business, and this is where I usually stay. Itâ€™s not super-glamorous, but it has all the elements I look for: in-room fridge and microwave; vanity separate from shower; comfy bed; flat-screen TV; plenty of room. I like the King Studio room--itâ€™s very roomy and open. The TV swings around so you can see it from the bed or sofa. Thereâ€™s tons of desk/counter space, which really helps me spread my stuff out for a week-long stay.  The only quibbles I have is that the internet speed really s*cks, but thatâ€™s typical for most hotels. Hotels just havenâ€™t figured out yet that business travelers need fast internet, and if we find it weâ€™ll be a regular.  Parking is in a garage, so thatâ€™s nice when itâ€™s raining. It costs extra tho--I think itâ€™s $15 or so. Thereâ€™s no restaurant, but I donâ€™t care because hotel food is usually ick.  The front desk people are usually pretty friendly. All in all, I prefer this to the other Galleria-area hotels.',608401,00000000099),
(00112658171,'2011-06-10','May',2011,0,'F',4,4,3,4,5,4,'Very nice','As with most JW Mâ€™s, this place is very nice. Itâ€™s huge so get ready to do a little walking. The hotel had â€™â€™greetersâ€™â€™ standing at key forks in the hallways to make sure you didnâ€™t get lost--that was really excellent. Loved having the Starbucks in the hotel. Food is excellent. Rooms just a teeny bit on the small side, but bathroom is roomy. The only design flaw is the bathroom door swings open and stops right in front of the toilet. Hotel is massive.  I liked it. Iâ€™d stay again. It IS out in the boondocks, though--not close to anything.',1584731,00000000099),
(00113169498,'2011-06-13','June',2011,0,'F',4,4,NULL,NULL,5,4,'Always a great experience','This is my second time staying at this hotel - both times for business. It is close to everything. The staff is always professional and easy to work with and the rooms are clean and well appointed. I would highly recommend this hotel as a great place to stay in Indianapolis.',88186,00000000043),
(00113174956,'2011-06-13','March',2011,0,'F',3,3,NULL,NULL,4,3,'Nice property','Stayed here for a convention. Walking distance to the convention center and close to 6th street where all the nightlife happens. Nice accommodations but ask for an exterior room.',98453,00000000043),
(00113191919,'2011-06-13','May',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,4,'Nice hotel on the University of Houston campu','We only stayed one night while visiting the University of Houston, but it was very enjoyable. As part of their program, there are many students involved in running the hotel. They were very courteous and helpful. It is a very nice hotel and well worth staying at if you are visiting the campus or just in the area.',108038,00000000010),
(00114387945,'2011-06-19','March',2011,1,'F',5,4,NULL,NULL,5,3,'AWESOME historic place!','bit pricy since the renovation, but still worth it. rich in history and ambience. we try to stay here as often as possible. if you love historic old places this is a gem!',93568,00000000072),
(00114388904,'2011-06-19','July',2010,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,3,'LUCKY US!','luckily we got an amazing rate for this POSH hotel...almost half the usual price. luxurious landmark hotel right across the street from the park (central park, that is). and everything in the room fridge is complimentary! gotta love that. if you want to do something special, and canâ€™t afford the plaza, this is the answer!',93559,00000000072),
(00114681412,'2011-06-23','June',2011,1,'F',4,4,NULL,NULL,4,4,'Good solid property','Stayed here as part of a wedding weekend. The rooms are basic and clean and nice to have space with the suites. The location is within walking distance of 6th street, convention center, etc. although a little further out than some other properties which equals a longer walk. If coming for a convention in any warm weather month, unless you plan to drive to the convention center I would recommend something a bit closer. Great access to S. Congress with itâ€™s unique restaurants and fun vibe. Overall a good value and would stay here again.',98420,00000000043),
(00114710799,'2011-06-24','June',2011,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Staff is Great','I just want to say that the staff was very helpful in getting my family an early check-in for a local wedding. Kelly was particularly helpful and I want to thank her very much!',93559,00000000070),
(00114837939,'2011-06-28','June',2011,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Great Event Venue!','Not only is this property in a great, central location, but itâ€™s a beautiful hotel as well! The banquet team canâ€™t be beat - everything was set up perfectly and were happy to help with last minute preparations. The catering was exceptional also. Extremely accommodating! We will be hosting our future seminars here!',1158926,00000000062),
(00114868866,'2011-06-29','June',2011,0,'F',3,3,NULL,NULL,4,4,'LOCATION','Location is perfect, but not all the rooms are fine. The first day we were on a room on the 3rd floor with an ugly interior view, no hot water, and they were not able to change the room till the next day,we had an interior regular view on the 10th floor, and everything was ok, nice amenities and free soft drinks on the fridge. Bad wi fi signal on both rooms. Jummeirah essex house is a much better option with same location and very similar prices.',93559,00000000061),
(00114911479,'2011-06-30','February',2011,2,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Great Downtown Location!','This is by far the nicest Best Western I have ever been to while on vacation. My husband and I stayed here on a weekend get-away for his birthday. The woman working the front desk was super polite and helpful - she called us a cab and even made dinner reservations for us before our concert at the House of Blues! The service was much better then I thought we would get. The room was HUGE, super clean and very comfy. We got turn down service twice while we were there and found our mini bar restocked each time we came back to our room. When heading back to Houston, I will make it a point to book this hotel.',239853,00000000013),
(00115097641,'2011-07-06','July',2011,0,'F',4,4,NULL,NULL,2,4,'Nice New Hotel.... but Front Desk and Breakfa','We stayed on a weekend. Nice new hotel, recently built, very clean. Valet staff was great - especially Jose/Diya. Front desk staff was polite but impersonal, very sterile. Answered your questions but with no warmth or inclination to be delightful and with one word replies. I am a gold SPG member and they pretended they had no upgraded rooms available. I persisted and told them I knew hotel was mostly vacant. Which is when they relented and upgraded me. Club floor lounge evening host was very nice and friendly, genuinely seeking to go above and beyond. Breakfast in the morning was a let down. Not refilled even when items ran out and not enough variety to begin with. Very easy skywalk access to the adjoining mall. Overall not a bad stay. But staff needed quite a bit of polishing and training.',1966350,00000000113),
(00115122824,'2011-07-07','May',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Our dream wedding came alive!','My husband and I had our wedding there May 7th and I want to thank the staff, specially the Wedding Coordinator and catering manager Ms. Dennis and Mr. Marco, Food and Beverage Hotel Mngr. for going always ahead of us to please our needs.  Every detail for the big day was done perfect, the timing for everything planned the food WOW delicious, guests were amazed at the food and service while they waited with appetizers and drinks. Once the party started and dinner was served everyone was even more thrilled to see the different choices in the buffet line, set up with so many choices of fresh and luscious foods.  Our decorations were so elegant, and all the details I myself wanted such as little surprises through the night, or the way I wanted things to look, colors, chair covers, cake table, gift table, favors for guests, announcements, even our picture and sign table etcâ€¦ where done exactly as I had asked them. Having our wedding there was hassle free and with less planning from our part.  Everyone at the hotel was so friendly and we look forward to spending our next anniversary there as we can assure the next morningâ€™s breakfast after our wedding reception was so DELICOUS we didnâ€™t want to leave.  As for the hotel itself, it is beautiful, it smells still like new, the rooms are comfortable, the bathrooms close to the wedding reception were kept neat and clean, and the floors and decorations were so nice and pleasant to invite anyone to stay there. We also want to mention the nice appearance of the front staff and the waitress/clean crew for looking clean and professional.  Finally, we will keep staying at the Hilton family and would like to say one more time thanks to the Hilton Garden Inn for making it possible to have our dream wedding come true!!! Love Diana and Marvin Gonzalez',1158926,00000000058),
(00115166186,'2011-07-08','July',2011,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Amazing hotel with an incredible staff','This hotel is absolutely beautiful. We have stayed here a few times now and we really donâ€™t ever want to stay anywhere else when we visit NYC. We have stayed in suites and rooms and even the rooms are very large. You canâ€™t beat a suite! No two are the same and they are all HUGE! The hotel is very quiet. We hardly ever see another person and we definitely donâ€™t hear a thing. The staff go out of there way to greet you and make sure that you have everything that you need. I canâ€™t imagine a nicer hotel in NYC. I HIGHLY recommend the Sherry Netherland!!',93559,00000000060),
(00115174547,'2011-07-09','January',2011,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Beautiful Hotel---Will return','Hotel was perfect. Recent remodel last year, rooms great, very, very clean bathrooms, glass showers, big vanities. University was closed, so ate in the ground floor restaurant. The french fries alone are worth a trip back. $15 cab ride from Hobby Airport. Had a single room for my niece who was starting school, suite for my wife and me. Stay here....youâ€™ll like it.',108038,00000000009),
(00115307077,'2011-07-13','June',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Elegance of a By-Gone Era','The Sherry-Netherland is most definitely a very unique and exceptional hotel. While I was staying there, I felt as if I were staying in an elegant pre-war Fifth Avenue co-op apartment. The old-world elegance and the attention to the details of hospitality (a hand-written welcome note from the manager, fresh flowers, a box of lovely chocolates, gratis beverages in the refrigerator, and white-gloved elevator operators) make The Sherry-Netherland a breath of fresh air in todayâ€™s cookie-cutter world of sameness and mediocrity. The Sherry-Netherland is heads and shoulders above its competition! Kudos to the exceptional staff---especially Renee and Russell. I look forword to my next stay at The Sherry!',93559,00000000056),
(00115389899,'2011-07-15','June',2011,0,'F',4,4,NULL,NULL,5,4,'Fantastic property - good for families and bu','Stayed for 3 days with family, have very few complaints. It is a grand old hotel in every sense of the word, but with modern, very nice touches. The in-house restaurant (Grant Grill) had one of the best menus and most supportive staff Iâ€™ve seen in years. Pricey, but worth every dime. Great feeling of history and place in the hotel. Had a bit of a tech issue late one night and the concierge (I wish I had gotten her name) was so helpful it really made an impression.   The down sides:  1. no pool, which is a disappointment if traveling with kids 2. they charge for internet, which is kind of cheap in this day and age (considering that most $69 a night airport hotels have it for free) 3. location is not as ideal as some of the places closer to the water, but still walking distance from whatever you want to see.   Overall I highly recommend and would go back anytime.',80668,00000000026),
(00115390312,'2011-07-15','May',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Consistently good','This was my 4th time at this property and it really makes sense as a location. 15 minutes from downtown/riverwalk, 20 minutes from 1604 loop where all the businesses are, 5 minutes from Alamo Quarry Mall - everything you need is right there. Free internet, free parking, clean, new and spacious rooms. Really a perfect choice for business travelers who donâ€™t want to get banged over the head at the riverwalk.',611291,00000000026),
(00115427304,'2011-07-16','July',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,4,'Great hotel in a great location','Took my wife to NYC for her 50th b-day. The hotel is beautiful inside and the decor in rooms etc. made us feel as if we went back in time to the early 1900â€™s but with modern amenities. Very ornate lobby and elevators (real live elevator operators) Great location at Central Park and within a 10 to 15 minute walk to Time Square and Broadway shows. We have stayed near Time Square in the past but wanted something less crazy and this place met our expectations. Also a short walk to Metropolitan Museum and You can pick up hop on hop off sightseeing buses, take carriage ride a block away from hotel. So for us it was convenient near attractions and less hectic than other parts of the city. We got a great price break and paid for three nights and got third for free. It is hard to find an inexpensive luxury hotel in this area. This hotel also has upscale residences in it.',93559,00000000055),
