(00115554209,'2011-07-19','July',2011,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Wonderful Stay','A couple friends of mine and I took a road trip from New Orleans to Houston for a baseball game. I used some SPG points to get a room for a nice price. The staff was amazing. We were kindly welcomed and treated so hospitably. Our pre-arrival was wonderful as Vickie Bellinghausen, Michael Andarge, and Jose Rodriguez all communicated with me about our stay. We were upgraded to a grand deluxe room with butler service and were very pleased with the large room size, furnishings and decor, and heavenly beds. Our view of this area of Houston was very nice. We took advantage of the awesome pool, sauna, fitness center, and locker room. Scott, the concierge, was wonderful with great suggestions for restaurants and arranging transportation for us in the house Mercedes. We were given a 4pm late check out which allowed us to really relax at the St. Regis and chill before heading downtown to the baseball game that evening. Our butler service was wonderful as we had cookies and fresh fruit awaiting us at arrival, had some garments pressed, and had morning coffee and tea at our wake-up call. I am a fan of St. Regis and the properties Iâ€™ve been blessed to stay in. Our only issue was being double charged after our check out (we paid with cash but still had a charge on the credit card for almost 2 weeks). Overall, we loved our experience and highly reccommend this hotel. Thanks St. Regis Houston.',107836,00000000107),
(00115616056,'2011-07-21','July',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,2,5,'Nice New Hotel','A couple of friends and I took a road trip from New Orleans to Houston to see the Astros/Red Sox game. Our first night in Houston was at the St. Regis. We decided to stay at the Westin the 2nd night because it is brand new, not too far from downtown, and had a good rate. We loved the property even though it seemed deserted. Iâ€™m sure they are still trying to get the word out about themselves. The lobby and public spaces were beautiful and modern. Our room was a typical Westin room with amazing beds and a great tv. I was a bit diappointed as the shower and tub were not separate like in most Westins Iâ€™ve stayed in. We greatly enjoyed the Executive Lounge with wonderful snacks and a decent breakfast. The pool and fitness center on the 18th floor were really cool. We enjoyed the view of Houston from up there. The pool was a bit chilly and hot tub not warm. Maybe they can work those kinks out. The Il Mulino restaurant was amazing. We were the only people in the whole place. But, I loved my chicken piccata and their award winning meatballs. The hotel is in a great location with Target, Cheesecake Factory, and Memorial City Mall across the street. The valet was helpful. No one really offered to help with luggage. At check-in, the gentleman was cordial but not genuinely friendly. He was a bit stiff and quite consumed with the rules such as asking to see my AAA card, telling me Iâ€™d probably not get SPG points since we held the room with my friendâ€™s credit card even though it was booked in my name and paid for in cash, and letting us know we had to use our room keys to access the elevator. Overall, we enjoyed our experience but prefer the St. Regis a few miles away because of their outstanding service.',1966350,00000000107),
(00115698385,'2011-07-23','July',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Great Place','I have been to midtown Manhattan many times and have stayed in a variety of hotels. This place has been the best. Nice, quiet hotel near Central Park...not noisy like the hotels near Times Square. Never had to wait for an elevator. The place has white gloved elevator operators! Rooms are nice and big and super clean. Right across the street from the Plaza if you are in the mood for some drinks. Within walking distance of everything. Will stay here again...just loved it!',93559,00000000054),
(00115828804,'2011-07-27','July',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Outstanding service inspite of HUGE event (Co','I was surprised to get a reservation using Marriott points since the hotel was â€™â€™sold outâ€™â€™. I figured the trade off for the free room would be that the service would be lacking, but I was wrong! Check in was a breeze (and when I realized I left my purse in my car, the valet brought my car back within 5 minutes), the room was on the small side but well appointed. I was only charged for self parking even though we had to valet park as the self parking was full. A late check was allowed. Only compliant was the bell hop who offered to show me where my bags could be stored after checkout but walked/ran ahead of me and did not offer to help carry my bags to the area on the far side of the lobby. Overall, this was the perfect place to stay for Comic Con and I would stay here again when I return to SD.',80227,00000000065),
(00115845530,'2011-07-27','July',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'The best hotel in New York City!!','We have been coming to New York City since I was a little boy, and I know all of the finest hotels in the city very well. I am now in my sixties, and there is no other hotel I would stay at in the city besides the Sherry. The rooms are beautiful, the location is the best, the staff is genuinely caring, they are like a family. And it is truly a value, not a rip-off like most other hotels in the city.',93559,00000000053),
(00115919449,'2011-07-28','July',2011,1,'F',4,4,NULL,NULL,5,5,'A good LAX choice...','Iâ€™ve stayed at the Sheraton Gateway numerous times, when LAX was part of my plans. This time much was the same...decent room, predictable airport transfer, helpful front desk and concierge...and itâ€™s still on my airport list. Of course, it used to be better...todayâ€™s Starbucks is pretty tired, Italian restaurant canâ€™t hold a candle to the old Shula Steak House...but the workout space is definitely improved. Stay away from Room 904...I had no end of internet connection problems. All in all, a dependable hotel.',78046,00000000052),
(00115922711,'2011-07-28','July',2011,1,'F',4,4,NULL,NULL,5,4,'Kimpton hotels are always fun...','Itâ€™s always a pleasure to stay at a Kimpton hotel, and the Palomar was no different, with its evening wine pours, smiling and helpful staff, eclectic decor and free cookies and milk for my daughter. Without question, the location is also great, with easy taxi access from National Airport, Rock Creek Park near to hand, Dupont Circle a transport/food/fun center just blocks away. The pool was a haven, but our room was very odd...quite large, except for the puny one-person-only bathroom -- very irritating. Try to get a room facing the street and definitely ask for a decent sized bathroom!',84093,00000000052),
(00115924691,'2011-07-28','July',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,4,'Youâ€™ll feel iike a Rich Uncle...','This is the way it must have been for my mom in New York City in the â€™50â€™s...like visiting your dowager aunt living quietly in elegance on the Upper East Side. Today, itâ€™s mostly a residence with fifty or so rooms available. Ours was a suite on the tenth floor, loads of space, a deco bathroom, a kitchenette filled with complimentary soft drinks (a lovely touch)...my daughter left a note saying â€™â€™I (loveheart) this hotelâ€™â€™ which just about sums up our visit. A particular pleasure was our interchanges with the elevator operators...of course we could have pushed the buttons ourselves, but how enjoyable to have a real person watching out for you. We also loved the back entrance to Ciprianiâ€™s...we felt very sophisticated sitting at the four seat bar having a Martini (ask for a â€™â€™Hemingwayâ€™â€™). The Sherry isnâ€™t the newest or coolest midtown hotel, but it continues to deliver an elegance of another time...an experience youâ€™ll surely enjoy.',93559,00000000052),
(00115938233,'2011-07-28','July',2011,2,'F',2,2,NULL,NULL,1,3,'Better off elsewhere','This is a cute, kitzchy boutique hotel with lots of upside potential. Unfortunately, poor customer service abounds and kills any positive attributes. The room I booked was unavailable when I checked in even though I had booked several months earlier. They offered to move me to the correct type of room for day two of my stay which just meant I could never get settled. I had to ask about parking and was directed to a side street because the hotel lot was full. The front desk clerk had to be asked everything and offered no info on his own. I finally started dealing with the shift manager. I inquired about restaurant options for dinner and the front desk didnâ€™t even recommend the restaurant right in the hotel. That should have been a sign., Ordered dinner at the restaurant on night two and of the two items I ordered, both were prepared incorrectly and not to my request at all.  The rooms are well appointed although the common areas were a bit dirty and I donâ€™t think the halls ever got vacuumed. This hotel desparately needs so solid customer service training and they might have a chance but as things stand I would prefer to spend slightly more on my room and stay at a more recognizable brand name and get consistent service and attention. Great bar area but that is not what draws me to a hotel. Too many failed opportunities and too many mistakes to warrant coming here again.',108306,00000000043),
(00115946241,'2011-07-29','July',2011,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Business luxury at its best.','I booked a room here to coach a writing client on her upcoming book, and it was the perfect place for it. The rooms are appointed with a long glass-topped surface spanning the entire drawers/fridge/desk, making it ideal for spreading out presentations, paperwork, or in our case, the book manuscript. The infinity pool and the hot tub on the 18th floor was a fabulous place to get away from it all, and so was the 024 bar with the super blue waterfall in its midst. Rich linens, thick towels, a bathrobe, double showerheads, and suede-like chairs, made this business trip a luxury I am eager to repeat! Perfect location across from the mall and restaurants, too. All floors accessible by room key only, including pool area.',1966350,00000000106),
(00115953912,'2011-07-29','July',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'My favorite hotel in New York','There is no question the Palace is the best hotel in New York for the money. It has it all, large clean rooms, helpful staff, great food. The midtown location is great for both business and pleasure. My only complaint relates to the prices in Gilt, the fantastic onsite bar. It cost a small fortune just for a single glass of wine. However this is a minor negative to an overall fantastic experience. The Palace has been my home away from home 4-5 times per year for the past 10 years and will continue to be for the foreseeable future. If you go, make it a point to tip the doormen, concierge and porters, your appreciation will be rewarded!',126260,00000000114),
(00115965957,'2011-07-29','May',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Great Hotel and Great Service','This hotel is one of my favorites! The staff is first class and will help you with any needs, whether you forgot your shaving kit, need a restaurant recommendation or need a ride to a restaurant they are there to serve you. When staying here make sure you get to know Sonny. Sonny has helped my business colleagues and me with dinner recommendations and then given us rides to the restaurants.  This is a great hotel for business, is close to downtown and is in the area they call mid-town, which appears to be going through a bit of a renaissance. Many restaurants, bars, cafes, coffee shops etc near by. I will be staying here again.',239853,00000000012),
(00116028751,'2011-07-30','June',2011,0,'F',4,4,NULL,NULL,5,3,'An OK hotel, a good Hilton experience.','I stayed at this hotel based on a search from my limited list of preferred flags and probably would not have picked it if Iâ€™d been driving looking for it. Itâ€™s hard to outrun â€™80s design but Iâ€™m also learning itâ€™s hard to stay on Westheimer for less than $200/night and would rather stay in one of these than a stick-and-brick 3- or 4-story budget-branded hotel. Room was fine, I still donâ€™t get having water bottles in the room not clearly marked if theyâ€™re complimentary or not. But it had a good HD plasma and an HD receiver (not always the case), finishes were reasonably up to date, good bedding, and the usual solid Hilton staff service. Only a short 1-night stay so I didnâ€™t experience anything else at the hotel.',99132,00000000090),
(00116111835,'2011-08-01','July',2011,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Awesome Property','We had a/c problems this past weekend so decided to stay here to get away from the heat and leaking problems! It was wonderful from start to finish! LaLa at the front was very nice and made sure our evening was a good one! We used the pool and hot tub and enjoyed it. Was nice to destress a little from the problems back at the house. We had a quiet nightâ€™s rest. The hotel is very warm and inviting from the staff to the rooms! Definitely recommend to anyone coming to the area! Thanks!',1158926,00000000057),
(00116209396,'2011-08-03','July',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Awesome hotel room, great location and brilli','I had the pleasure of staying at the Sherry-Netherland for one night only which was such a shame as it is brilliant. On my arrival I was ever so nicely greeted and looked after by the front desk.  My room was 1111 and I can honestly say that when I entered it my jaw hit the floor. It is massive. The lounge is big and can certainly be used to host a drink reception. There is a kitchen area, small but does the job. The bedroom was big as well and the bed ................ one of the most comfortable I have ever slept on, especially the pillows. As soft as anything. The location is great on 5th Avenue, at the south end of Central Park and north end of the shops.  Would I stay there again . Absolutely.',93559,00000000051),
(00116232135,'2011-08-03','July',2011,0,'F',4,5,NULL,NULL,5,4,'Modern hotel in a great downtown location.','Stayed here 2 nights with our 2 young kids. The hotel is very clean and modern. Great downtown location within walking distance to most sites. The staff was friendly and helpful. Only negative was there was no bathtub in the room, only a shower, which made bathing our youngest difficult. We would stay here again.',1200603,00000000115),
(00116309180,'2011-08-05','July',2011,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Amazing stay, amazing staff, WOW!!! The best ','We have been planning for this trip a long time, first time for my children to to New York!!, I have three boys, ages 7, 11, and 14, picking them up from Camp in upstate New York. We stayed for 13 nights!! can you imagine? Where do I start........everything was truly exceptional, the rooms that we where assigned to...perfect one bedroom suite with a sofa bed on the other room, a kitchenette that saved us a bunch of expenses by having cereal or a sandwich now and then, and also feeling like residents a bit. In front of our suite, a room for my other two boys, also perfect, the decoration, very clean and luxurious..........and the beds are the most cozy and confortable beds we have ever experienced in any hotel, and we have been all over the world. The staff, how we felt welcomed with gifts for our kids, sodas and water for free every day and the amazing service worth mentioning Tammy at the front desk, she is the best!! and Kristina Kinet, Thank you for everything!!!',93559,00000000050),
(00116368196,'2011-08-07','August',2011,3,'F',3,4,NULL,NULL,1,2,'Disappointed. Our discount applied to our ser','My wife and I came and stayed here for business meetings (not held onsite). The property seems charming enough, some might consider the 50â€™s/60â€™s California Ranch style â€™â€™datedâ€™â€™ but I consider it classic, but truthfully we didnâ€™t have time to explore beyond our room, main lobby, and veranda (restaurant & bar space), and we didnâ€™t play golf, use the spa or enjoy any of the propertyâ€™s amenities, including what appears to be a nice kidâ€™s program. So why are we disappointed? By the weak service of waitstaff and lack of service by front desk/security/valet staff handling (or lack thereof) of our complaints over two nights. Our first night was marred by a car alarm that went off ALL NIGHT LONG, a beep-beep-beep that cycled on for a couple minutes, off for maybe 10-30 minutes, then on again. First call to front desk was theyâ€™d send security. My second call was answered by someone who had just come on and didnâ€™t know anything about it but would send security. I slept through the alarms until the one that woke me at 5:30 am but my wife had not slept. So I walked to the front desk and the gal there said she didnâ€™t know anything about it but then jumped on the radio to someone saying â€™â€™what do you know about that black Honda Civic in Valet with the alarm thatâ€™s been going off?â€™â€™ Nice. Second night, and unbelievably, another car alarm was going off into the night, this one being one of those with six different alarm sounds. Thank God it ended sometime after midnight, maybe thatâ€™s when the offender who had self-parked his pickup truck in the valet lot and left, returned. First call, theyâ€™ll send security. Second call was met with hostility, â€™â€™thereâ€™s nothing we can do, valet doesnâ€™t have a key, weâ€™ve looked in the bar and asked everyone if itâ€™s their truck. Sorry, letâ€™s just hope the owner comes back.â€™â€™ Third was an in-person visit to the front desk who says Iâ€™m the only one complaining about it. He radios the valet who says sorry, he didnâ€™t find keys or the owner and heâ€™s off in 5 minutes so he canâ€™t helpâ€™â€™ but theyâ€™ll send security, give them a little more time, and theyâ€™ll call me and tell me what theyâ€™re going to do. No call... ...no apologies, no offer to move us to another room, or comp us, or offer SOMETHING.  We (including coworkers) had cocktails on the veranda 3 times and 3 times waitstaff was inattentive, one time disappearing with my wifeâ€™s credit card and had to be located after we waited 30 minutes.for her return. We stayed at a corporate-discounted room rate. I guess thatâ€™s why we ended up in the â€™â€™Terracesâ€™â€™, the rooms that are outward-facing, towards the parking lots, on the perimeter of the resort (and why we were not offered a relocation?). Nice rooms, well-appointed, with attractive casework for dresser, desk and 42â€™â€™ plasma with digital LodgeNet, and another nice piece which set the king bed at a 45-degree angle, and with integrated night lighting. If the rest of the resort has this level of appointment then youâ€™ll be fine. But rooms 801-831, with their single-pane windows, should be avoided, due to poor proximity to parking areas.',218770,00000000090),
(00116368453,'2011-08-07','July',2011,0,'F',2,3,NULL,NULL,3,4,'Very average hotel','Hmm, not sure where to start. The hotel is very average and while nothing was specifically wrong, you can do so much better in this town.  Check in staff was very busy. 1 person was manning the desk. They have this ridiculous no-party policy. We have to sign that. (I hate signing other peopleâ€™s policy. The hotel has a no-party policy. I appreciate that. I do not want to sign it. I am sure someday someone will bring a lawsuit). The room smells moldy and like a chemical wash. The suites are very large and well appointed. As a first for me in my 20 year traveling life, they upgraded the old CRTs to the new LCDs during my 8-days stay (this was planned by the hotel -- I was just staying there). There is a kitchenette and a fridge (which opened the wrong way).  The shower was just OK -- bad pressure and bad water temperature. The location is great and I would stay again here only if my other favorite hotels in the area are sold out.',98954,00000000101),
(00116368504,'2011-08-07','July',2011,1,'F',4,5,NULL,NULL,4,5,'Very nice, new Westin','I love staying at Westinâ€™s and this was a good stay. This is not an excellent place for Platinum recognition, but the stay was very good. The hotel is new and everything works. As with all Westinâ€™s that I have been in, the bed was excellent and the shower was superb. The bathroom lighting was very nice. I got a room that was on the diagonal end, so my bath was very long -- that was a nice touch. I had to pay for parking, so was not happy about that. Will surely stay again here.',1966350,00000000101),
(00116497530,'2011-08-09','June',2011,2,'F',4,5,NULL,NULL,5,1,'Not sure what the big deal is','First time that I stayed here and iâ€™m not sure i get what the big deal is. Room was nice and the service excellent.  The gym was in great condition and one of the attendants gave me a glass of water while I was running on the treadmill (iâ€™ve never got that level of service before)! The restaurant was okay ~ getting a table outside the bar in the evening was painful as there were often 1-2 people on tables that sat 5-6 (our group was 6). Still, the relative value of the room was much lower than the actual price paid.',76049,00000000102),
(00116572788,'2011-08-11','August',2011,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Simply Awesome','Went there for our 10th wedding anniversary and were completely taken aback by the staff and hotel. Iâ€™ve never in my life seen such quality service. You are made to feel as if you own the whole hotel. Everywhere you go, you are greeted with smiles and friendly comments. If you want a truly amazing experience and many wonderful memories and are going to NYC, put this hotel at the top of your list. Thank you to all the staff @ the Sherry ...there are too many of you to name specifically, but you were all awesome !! Weâ€™ll be back ASAP.',93559,00000000040),
(00116678911,'2011-08-13','August',2011,1,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'An absolutely wonderful hotel with welcoming ','This was our familyâ€™s 4th stay at The Sherry-Netherland. We absolutely love it. Perfect location, updated rooms, great beds, incredibly clean, marble finishes in the bathrooms, flatscreen TVs, tons of bathroom amenities, etc. Our kids are made to feel welcome, each received a personalized gift bag with goodies inside. These are the little things that show the staff really cares. I canâ€™t praise this hotel and its staff enough. We will be back.',93559,00000000039),
(00116877473,'2011-08-18','December',2010,0,'F',5,5,NULL,NULL,5,5,'Best place for New Years in New York City','Pricing on-par for top hotels in New York, worth every penny to me. Quiet elegance inside for escaping the activity of outside.',113298,00000000037),
